This paper discusses modifications to the relay selection and circuit selection processes in the Tor anonymity system to improve performance while maintaining anonymity. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a new path selection algorithm, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the security implications of the proposed modifications, which could fall under cryptography and security (cs.CR) or performance analysis (cs.PF).
